Below are some common, legitimate ways to deny or restrict access:

Nginx: deny all traffic
- In the server block:
  location / {
    deny all;
  }
- Reload: sudo nginx -t && sudo systemctl reload nginx

Nginx: allow only specific IPs (deny everyone else)
- In the server block:
  location / {
    allow 203.0.113.10;
    allow 2001:db8::1;
    deny all;
  }

Apache (.htaccess): deny all
- In your site root .htaccess:
  Require all denied

Apache: allow specific IPs
- In .htaccess:
  Require ip 203.0.113.10
  Require ip 2001:db8::/32
  Require all denied

Node.js (Express): block by IP
- Middleware example:
  const blocked = new Set(['203.0.113.10']);
  app.use((req, res, next) => {
    const ip = req.ip;
    if (blocked.has(ip)) return res.status(403).send('Forbidden');
    next();
  });

Node.js (Express): require a secret token
- Middleware:
  app.use((req, res, next) => {
    if (req.get('X-Access-Token') !== process.env.ACCESS_TOKEN) {
      return res.status(403).send('Forbidden');
    }
    next();
  });

Python (Flask): block by IP
- Example:
  from flask import Flask, request, abort
  app = Flask(__name__)
  BLOCKED = {'203.0.113.10'}
  @app.before_request
  def deny():
    if request.remote_addr in BLOCKED:
      abort(403)

Django: maintenance mode (deny all except staff)
- Middleware approach or use ALLOWED_HOSTS with a reverse proxy rule; simple view:
  from django.http import HttpResponseForbidden
  def maintenance(request):
      return HttpResponseForbidden("Service temporarily unavailable")
- Map urls to maintenance and configure web server to route all paths there when needed.

Cloudflare: block rules
- Create a Firewall Rule: Field = IP Source Address, Operator = equals, Value = 203.0.113.10, Action = Block.
- For maintenance: set a rule Action = Block for Path contains “/”.

AWS WAF: block all except whitelisted
- Create a Web ACL with an IP set for allowed addresses.
- Add a default action = Block, rule to Allow for the IP set.

Rate limiting instead of full deny (to mitigate abuse)
- Nginx:
  limit_req_zone $binary_remote_addr zone=api:10m rate=10r/s;
  location /api/ {
    limit_req zone=api burst=20 nodelay;
  }

Serving a maintenance page (user-friendly deny)
